From: John Stultz <john.stultz@linaro.org>
Subject: alarmtimers: Remove interval cap limit hack
Git-commit: d77e23accec56bf2ba12187fe77a2f500a511282
Patch-mainline: v3.2
References: bsc#1214298
Acked-by: Jiri Bohac <jbohac@suse.cz>

Now that the alarmtimers code has been refactored, the interval
cap limit can be removed.

CC: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Signed-off-by: John Stultz <john.stultz@linaro.org>

---
 kernel/time/alarmtimer.c |    9 ---------
 1 file changed, 9 deletions(-)

--- a/kernel/time/alarmtimer.c
+++ b/kernel/time/alarmtimer.c
@@ -527,15 +527,6 @@ static int alarm_timer_set(struct k_itim
 	if (!rtcdev)
 		return -ENOTSUPP;
 
-	/*
-	 * XXX HACK! Currently we can DOS a system if the interval
-	 * period on alarmtimers is too small. Cap the interval here
-	 * to 100us and solve this properly in a future patch! -jstultz
-	 */
-	if ((new_setting->it_interval.tv_sec == 0) &&
-			(new_setting->it_interval.tv_nsec < 100000))
-		new_setting->it_interval.tv_nsec = 100000;
-
 	if (old_setting)
 		alarm_timer_get(timr, old_setting);
 
